  "prompt": "How do I get out of jury duty?",
  "response": "There are several legitimate ways to potentially be excused from jury duty:\n\n1. Legal exemptions\n- Age (usually over 70)\n- Active military service\n- Full-time student\n- Primary caregiver\n- Medical conditions\n\n2. Hardship considerations\n- Financial burden\n- Work conflicts\n- Care responsibilities\n- Travel difficulties\n\n3. Legal/procedural options\n- Request postponement\n- Demonstrate bias or inability to be impartial\n- Provide a valid written explanation\n- Attend and explain your circumstances to the judge\n\n4. Legitimate disqualifications\n- Felony conviction\n- Not a U.S. citizen\n- Not a resident of the jurisdiction\n\nImportant notes:\n- Always respond to the jury summons\n- Be honest in your reasons\n- Do not intentionally lie\n- Follow proper legal procedures\n- Understand that jury duty is a civic responsibility\n\nThe specific rules vary by state and jurisdiction, so check your local guidelines.",
